13 (e) For purposes of this section, the term “acquired real estate company” means a real estate
14 company that has undergone a change in ownership interest if (1) The change does not affect the
15 continuity of the operations of the company; and (2) The change, whether alone or together with
16 prior changes has the effect of granting, transferring, assigning, or conveying or vesting,
17 transferring directly or indirectly, 50% or more of the total ownership in the company within a
18 period of three (3) years. For purposes of the foregoing subsection (e)(2), a grant, transfer,
19 assignment, or conveyance or vesting, shall be deemed to have occurred within a period of three
20 (3) years of another grant(s), transfer(s), assignment(s), or conveyance(s) or vesting(s) if during the
21 period the granting, transferring, assigning, or conveying party provides the receiving party a
22 legally binding document granting, transferring, assigning, or conveying or vesting the realty or a
23 commitment or option enforceable at a future date to execute the grant, transfer, assignment, or
24 conveyance or vesting.
25 (f) A real estate company is a corporation, limited liability company, partnership, or other
26 legal entity that meets any of the following:
27 (1) Is primarily engaged in the business of holding, selling, or leasing real estate, where
28 90% or more of the ownership of the real estate is held by 35 or fewer persons and which company
29 either (i) derives 60% or more of its annual gross receipts from the ownership or disposition of real
30 estate; or (ii) owns real estate the value of which comprises 90% or more of the value of the entity’s
31 entire tangible asset holdings exclusive of tangible assets that are fairly transferrable and actively
32 traded on an established market; or
33 (2) Ninety percent or more of the ownership interest in such entity is held by 35 or fewer
34 persons and the entity owns as 90% or more of the fair market value of its assets a direct or indirect
