1 interest in a real estate company. An indirect ownership interest is an interest in an entity 90% or
2 more of which is held by 35 or fewer persons and the purpose of the entity is the ownership of a
3 real estate company.
4 (g) In the case of a grant, assignment, transfer, or conveyance or vesting that results in a
5 real estate company becoming an acquired real estate company, the grantor, assignor, transferor, or
6 person making the conveyance or causing the vesting, shall file or cause to be filed with the division
7 of taxation, at least five (5) days prior to the grant, transfer, assignment, or conveyance or vesting,
8 notification of the proposed grant, transfer, assignment, or conveyance or vesting, the price, terms
9 and conditions thereof, and the character and location of all of the real estate assets held by the real
10 estate company and shall remit the tax imposed and owed pursuant to subsection (a). Any such
11 grant, transfer, assignment, or conveyance or vesting which results in a real estate company
12 becoming an acquired real estate company shall be fraudulent and void as against the state unless
13 the entity notifies the tax administrator in writing of the grant, transfer, assignment, or conveyance
14 or vesting as herein required in subsection (g) and has paid the tax as required in subsection (a).
15 Upon the payment of the tax by the transferor, the tax administrator shall issue a certificate of the
16 payment of the tax which certificate shall be recordable in the land evidence records in each
17 municipality in which such real estate company owns real estate. Where the real estate company
18 has assets other than interests in real estate located in Rhode Island, the tax shall be based upon the
19 assessed value of each parcel of property located in each municipality in the state of Rhode Island.
20 (h) In addition to the tax imposed by subsections (a) and (b) of this section, the city of
21 Providence is authorized to impose by ordinance, on each deed, instrument, or writing by which
22 any lands, tenements, or other realty sold in the city of Providence, in which an interest is granted,
23 assigned, transferred, or conveyed to, or vested in, the purchaser or purchasers, or any other person
24 or persons, by his, her, or their direction, or on any grant, assignment, transfer, or conveyance or
25 such vesting, by such persons that has an interest in real estate, when the consideration paid exceeds
26 one million dollars ($1,000,000), a tax at the rate of up to three-quarters of one percent (0.75%) of
27 the purchase price that is paid for the purchase of property or the interest in an acquired real estate
28 company (inclusive of the value of any lien or encumbrance remaining at the time the sale, grant,
29 assignment, transfer, or conveyance or vesting occurs, or in the case of an interest in an acquired
30 real estate company, a percentage of the value of such lien or encumbrance equivalent to the
31 percentage interest in the acquired real estate company being granted, assigned, transferred,
32 conveyed, or vested). The tax, if imposed, is payable at the time of making, the execution, delivery,
33 acceptance, or presentation for recording of any instrument affecting such transfer, grant,
34 assignment, transfer, conveyance, or vesting. In the absence of an agreement to the contrary, the
